de.semp.medical.spo2

Class SpO2emulated

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.semp.medical.spo2.SpO2Sensor
      • de.semp.medical.spo2.SpO2emulated
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IPatientEmu

    public class SpO2emulated
extends SpO2Sensor
implements IPatientEmu
    A virtual sensor which emulates sensor data from a virtual patient. Parameters of the patient can be modified. The actual values are simulated using a random process. The variance depends on the parameters of the simulated patient.

      • setParam

        public boolean setParam(java.lang.String param,
                        java.lang.String value)
        Set parameters of the patient.
        Specified by:
        setParam in interface IPatientEmu
        Parameters:
        param - the name of the parameter to be set. Available parameters are: BPM: simulated mean heart rate of the patient SpO2: simulated mean spo2 value of the patient norm: normal simulated values low: low simulated values high: high simulated values
        value - the value to be set for the given parameter.
        Returns:
        true, if parameter exists, false otherwise.
